\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 -}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yesXC_ibRKE"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yesXC_ibRKE}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\plain {Addiction to a person is a greater thing}
\par\plain 
\par\plain {The greatest cause of relapse is codependent relationships. It does so much damage. One of the hardest things to deal with because it plays off natural human needs, realtionships, love, belonging. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Everybody that is codependent has complex trauma.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Damages sense of identity.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The reasons why im being negelected is because something is wrong with me. Core identity called shame. Makes a child survive and try to stay safe \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0  it makes a healthy relationship impossible because of shame. They don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know how to make them healthy, and so they get wounded over and over again.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Because they are obsessed with keeping safe, they are setting up the opposite- relationships where they keep getting hurt.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Codependent: one person supporting or trying to solve the other person\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s problems. Meet their self esteem and emotional needs. On person or both persons ends up becomes an enabler of the other persons unhealthy behavior. So you try to support them, but what you are supporting is their immature and irresponsible behavior. Cleaning up their messes. But you\u8217\'92re giving them permission to never grow up. It ends up being like a parent and a child. Supporting unhealthy behaviors.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Enabler becomes totally occuppied with solving the other person\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s problems, and trying to meet their needs, and they totally lose track of their own needs. Living without their own needs being met. They\u8217\'92re dying inside, trying to give life to someone else, who doesn\u8217\'92t want life.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 It\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s like addiction, it gradually gets worse and worse, and those in it get sicker and sicker and sicker. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Acouple things about addiction that apply.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 1.) codependency can be you\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re addicted to a person. They\u8217\'92re your crackpipe. Make me feel alive. Solve all my pain problems. Solve all my emptiness. Give me life. Even when it gets to the point where you know the crackpipe is no longer giving you positive experiences, and is giving you hell, you can\u8217\'92t let go. Same is true in codependency. This person is becoming more and more toxic and destroying you, but can you get rid of them? No.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 2.) addiction to a relationship style that isn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t healthy}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab - if you look at the necessary ingredients for a healthy relationship - honesty, trust, respect, you don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t find those in a co-dependent relationship.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 3.) Codepenency is how a shame based person approaches relationships.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Complex trauma always happens in a situation, usually home, where the person with the most power is a narcissist.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Codependent relationships usually always have a narcissist\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Narcissist \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93 You\u8217\'92re selfish for having needs\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I can\u8217\'92t be convinced that you love me unless you have no friends and no family. Im going to start cutting out your friends and family and activity so I am the only person in your world. So you go ahead with it. Then he\u8217\'92s gonna say, you should put up with my anger, im just having a bad day. The line in the sand keeps moving to sacrifice your values and your morals. Now you start lying for them, covering for them, to keep them happy. You are getting sicker and sicker to accomodate their growing narcisism. Narcisist is the superior and you are the inferior.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 You don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t like yourself, you are uneasy with who you are.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I have these painful feelings, what do I need to do to fix it. The brain doesnt go, I need to fix my inside, because its concluded my inside is bad. So where is the solution going to come from- only way I can feel good about myself is if others have positive feelings about me. I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ll piggyback on their positive feelings. This is where codependency begins. Looking outside yourself to deal with shame, without dealing with it internally.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 How do I convince myself that I am lovable? I have to be in a relationship with somebody and that proves that they want to be in a relationship with me, can\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t be alone, because being alone proves to them that they are unlovable.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Either going to be a helper who rescues and gets validation, or a needy person, who is rescued.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Helper and a needy person as a basis for a relationship. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I can\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t be happy unless they\u8217\'92re happy. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Therefore, my priority now is im going to be responsible for their emotional world, and so if they have a problem im giong to try to fix it, if they\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re angry ill try to calm them up so they\u8217\'92re happy.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92m plugged into them, I don\u8217\'92t have a clue what I think. My identity is a reflection of theirs.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Healthy relationship - both parties make sacrifices about 50% of the time.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Child didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t have emotional honesty taught to them, it was punched down inside. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Codependency devlops in an emotional abusive environment with the narcissist being abusive, and it develops in an emotionally dishonest environment, because the enabler is never going to be honest about how things really are.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Soul wounds do not heal if ignored. They continue to shape and govern our emotions, self-image and our ways of interacting in relationships, long beyond the childhood in which they were received. Shame does damage far beyond the original dysfunction because it is damage the wounded souls unintentionally continue to perpetrate on themselves. It is a kind of soul murder.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Codependency is a defnece system that cuases us to wound ourselves- it allows people to survive physically but leaves them feeling dead and empty inside.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Complex trauma - phyiscally alive, soul dead.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Strictly control relationships so that no conflict appears.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Original DSM entry attempt:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Person who gets their self esteem from enduring an unhealthy relationship, and they keep others in it. They do this even though it is hurting everyone. Putting the needs of other people ahead of the person\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s own needs. Anxieties that arise from separation. Enmeshment which can arise. Unwillingness to draw appropriate boundaries. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Denial, holding back emotion, hypervigilance, anxiety, and they are stuck in it because they have no desire to get out. Clipping their own wings to stay in it. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Some people believe that narcissitic relationships largely remain in place because the partners are codependent enablers who participate in the toxic spiral because the narcissist feeds their vulnerabilities. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Theres a danger in all this of pathologizing a person for simply wanting to make a relationship work. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 I do believe that a certain percentage of narcissitic relationship dynamcis do reflect a co-dependent partner. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I believe that a substantial subset for whom education about these cycles, namely that narcissistic individuals are not going to change, and that they are indeed classical cycles that play out the same way, that you don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t need to personalize tham, it tends to set you free. So many people that are stuck in a narcissistic relationship, they are not stuck in codependency they may not be in denial, and they are aware of what is going on. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Co dependency is two people with shame issues trying to solve their shame problems.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Enlist someone outside of the relationship.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Codependncy isn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t a viallain, a bad guy. Its not, im such a piece of garbage im in a codependent relationship. What happens for a lot of guys is there is an immediate tendency to want to shame. What\u8217\'92s wrong with me? How do I kill that part off?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The reality is that codependency is not the enemy; what causes it is childhood.}
