\par\plain 
\par\plain 
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Codependency is a spectrum, mild to severe.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 In order for a narcissist to be in a relationship, theres got to be a conarcissist.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Holllly shit:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Complex trauma is living in danger all the time. You are constantly in survival mode - What happens in survival mode is you have to make your needs and your survival more important than the needs of others. So you put yourself in a narcissistic place. Your needs now matter more than anything else in the world. In event trauma, you put your need in front of everybody else\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s, until the danger passes, and then you come back down to feeling equal to everybody else, and you enter into loving relationships again where you value them and they value you just as much. The tragedy of complex trauma, is you are constantly living in danger, so you are constantly living with you mattering more than anybody else. So complex trauma sets you up to become a narcissist. Thats what survival mode 24/7 looks like. Your needs have to become more important than everybody else.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The other effect is that the child is abused/abandoned/neglected, and they conclude its their fault. That develops shame. The greater the abandonment, the more child personalizes that they must not matter at all, zero value. They develop a belief about themselve that they are less than. The greater the trauma, the greater the shame. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 So, narcissism is a response to severe shame. So when a person is in a place where they feel totally like they\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re nothing because of severe trauma, that is no fun to live with. That is way too depressing to live with, so the brain begins to develop ways of trying to get rid of that. So narcisissim is the brain doing everything possible to either deny that it has  any shame at all. It goes to the place that I am better than everybody. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A narcissist needs somebody adoring him all the time. That\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s how he\u8217\'92s fed. That creates a co-narcissist or a mirror, or an echo that reflects back to the narcissist. Feeds the narcisisst.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Co-narcissist is a shame response as well. They don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t try to compensate for their shame, they give into it. They\u8217\'92re depressed, feeling terrible, the live with that feeling all the time. They want a narcissist to be the sun of their world to come in shine their light on their world and say, I like you, I want to fix you, to let them know that they do have value. This person noticed me and wants to help me. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Now you have the sun and the planet working together. That is a narcissist and a conarcissist.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Children get neglected because narcissist is all wrapped up pursuing their selfish endeavors. The children get abandoned if they don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t cooperate with the narcissist. Children dont like living like that. Children in their own mind are trying to solve the family problems that arise when the narcissist is the sun in the family system. ANd so children will adopt different roles to fix the family and try to make the narcissist happy. So each child will try different things as a way to solve family problems and try to get the narcissist to meet their needs and validate them. So you get children who try to be the perfect child, do extra chores, etc. The comedian child, theres a whole lot of pain in this family, be funny and laughing all the time. The invisible child, ill have no needs, I will fade into the background, never ask for anything so that I don\u8217\'92t add any extra stress. What they\u8217\'92re going to find as they get older is that it didn\u8217\'92t fix a thing. The narcisst wasn\u8217\'92t happy, didn\u8217\'92t meet their needs, and they took it personally, and developed their own shame. And that creates the next generation of co-dependent people. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Eighteen criteria of a narcissist - meet at least half of them. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - they believe they are special and unique, a little bit better than everyone else. Think they can only be understood by special people. If you call them on their stuff, they have a comeback that says, you don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t get me because you\u8217\'92re not special.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - deep down, they believe they are more important than other people. Smarter, more capable, better.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - exaggerate their achievements.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - expect to be recognized by you as being better than you. Look up to them and adore them. In their private fantasy mind, they have fantasies about how successful they are and are going to be. That person said hi to me, they must be in love with me. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Insatiable appetite for praise or validation. Always looking for a pat on the back.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Thinks everyone is jealous of them. Thinks everyone wishes they could be like them. All about image. Dont feel good inside, but never admit that. Their focus is looking good.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -associate with a high status person. A good looking woman. I know the president of this and that, and drop names, and try to hang out with influential people.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Try to control how you think about them. If they do something that you think wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t appropriate, they send you emails to explain away what they did, and what you should conclude about them.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Arrogance. Nose is a little in the air. A bit of snobbishness.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - They must never be wrong. Their image says they always have to be right. They will never admit they\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re wrong, but rather they will take what happened and twist it to make you wrong. Take what you say and twist it to make you wrong.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - at first very caring, but as true colors come out, you find they dont have much empathy or care for other peoples needs or feelings at all. They feel entitled. A relationship is never 50/50, it is always lopsided.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - They don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t think rules apply to them. Rules apply to you, but not to me. I can go through your phone, you can\u8217\'92t go through mine. They are the exception to every rule.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - They are exploitive of others. All about manipulating you to meet their needs. They don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know how to love people, they know how to use people. In their minds they\u8217\'92re being loving, because they\u8217\'92re giving and kind in the early days, but they\u8217\'92re grooming you; giving to get. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - They must feel control and always get what they want. They can be the sweetest nicest people in the world 99% of the time, until they don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t get what they want. Then you got world war three. They will explode and there will be hell to pay to anyone who has crossed them. They can act very healthy until triggered, and it is the triggers that reveal their true stuff. They can no longer hide their deeper stuff once they get triggered. The masks come away. Main triggers are percieved rejection; if you say no to them, watch out. Not getting what they want, not getting enough attention, or anything that messes with their image. Usually they go to anger, and then they get cruel abusive, lash out, say hurtful things, and can be destructive. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0  they always have to be fed because they have a lot of jealousy issues. The only ways they can be convinced that they are the sun of the universe is if there\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s no one else in the universe but you. Jealousy kicks in and they get really cruel. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 extreme sensitivity and feeling of rejection over the slightest things. They pick up hurt easily because of all of their shame issues. But as soon as they feel hurt, it\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s not their issue, its yours, and call you selfish.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0  need a mirror. Need constant reflection.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A lot of shame deep down that they\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ve never acknowledged. Pretty sure that if people get to know them, no one will ever want to meet their needs. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Narcissist become master manipulators. So good at manipulating, your not aware. Usually a hidden agenda. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 3 different types of narcissist}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 1.) exhibitionist narcissist - outgoing, always talking about dreams and accomplishments. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab Put everybody else down a little bit or a lot.\tab Positive to themselves negative about everyone else.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 2.) Toxic/malignant narcissist - put themselves up , put others down - sadistic. Feel alive when they cause pain to other people. Bullies who thrives off of causing pain. Loves to create chaos. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 3.) Covert narcissist - the person who you dont think is a narcissist. Never put themselves out there. They seem deperessed and seem to hate themselves. Thats the co narcissist. They are saying please make everything all about me. If I love you enough, will you make your world about me for a little bit. They give and give and give hoping to one day be the center of your universe. They\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re still giving to getting. Their still narcissitistic. You just don\u8217\'92t see it until they\u8217\'92re in a relationship for a long time. }
