\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Okay, deep dive today was a huge mindfuck.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 At one point I was starting to try and pathologize myself, thinking like, am I a covert narc or just codependent? Am I love bombing? Am I only behaving the way I am to try and extract some sort of concession later? But then one dude mentioned that he thinks basically everyone is co-dependendent to some extent, because ultimately no parent is perfect, and that thought sort of brought me back down to reality. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The covert narc thought came from the following quote:  the covert narc thinks, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91If I love you enough, will you make your world about me for a little bit? They give and give and give hoping to one day be the center of your universe.\u8217\'92}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ve found myself, in moments, thinking thoughts like that. But then, the fact that they are only moments is reassures me, because on the whole I think my fascination with you is very much a result of the happiness it gives me, which is healthy. So to that end, I want to say that I think I have the basic tools to deal with this. And I can rely on your awareness and experience to notify me of any red flags in my behavior. I want to put this out there because one of those tools is completely open communication. }
